results.name: Number of new fractions m/n < 1, where (m,n)=1 and "new" means the value of mn has not occurred before.
reference: S. W. Golomb, personal communication, Svalbard, Norway, 7/97.
link: Andrew Howroyd, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000 (terms 1..1000 from T. D. Noe)
mathematica: a[n_] := Sum[Boole[GCD[i, n] == 1 && Sum[t = i*n/d; Boole[GCD[t, d] == 1 && t < d < n], {d, Divisors[i*n]}] == 0], {i, 1, n - 1}];
program: (PARI) a(n)=if(n==1, 1, sum(i=1, n-1, gcd(i,n) == 1 && 0==sumdiv(i*n, d, my(t=i*n/d); gcd(t,d)==1 && d<n && t<d))) \\ _Andrew Howroyd_, Nov 16 2018
results.author: _N. J. A. Sloane_
